17/04/2011
ANKARA, Turkey â With elections approaching in June, Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan presented his ruling Justice and Development Party's (AKP) manifesto on Saturday (April 16th).
Pledging that the government will work to make Turkey one of the top ten economies in the world, it focuses on such areas as technology, job creation, highway construction, increased exports and boosting tourism.
Erdogan reaffirmed that EU membership remains the AKP's strategic goal.
The Kurdish issue in Turkey, meanwhile, would be resolved "on the basis of freedoms and democracy", he said.
Erdogan also announced that his party will start work on a new constitution after the elections.
(Anadolu news agency, World Bulletin, Xinhua - 16/04/11)
